RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLAME D RULE MAKER , rated well off the rail down the backstretch, moved up in the two path on the far turn, found room between horses entering the stretch, closed steadily outside COAST ALONG and was up near the finish. UNION LEAGUE chased the pace outside foes down the backstretch, raced in the three path on the far turn and gave way. SERGEANT SHERMAN was not a factor. SILK PRINCE , wide both turns, gave way. DELACROIX , steadied when getting in at the break, was outrun. FAZZANI , outrun, pulled up on the far turn and walked off.
